4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT AUTHORIZING THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH AND
5 HUMAN SERVICES TO LIMIT CERTAIN FOODS BASED ON RECOMMENDATIONS FROM THE PANEL ON
6 FOOD SAFETY; CREATING THE PANEL ON FOOD SAFETY; PROVIDING QUALIFICATIONS FOR THE
7 PANEL; REQUIRING THE ADOPTION AND ENFORCEMENT OF RULES BY THE DEPARTMENT OF
8 PUBLIC HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES WITH ASSISTANCE FROM THE UNITED STATES FOOD AND
9 DRUG ADMINISTRATION; ESTABLISHING REPORTING REQUIREMENTS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS
10 50-1-202, 50-31-108, 50-31-109, AND 80-1-104, MCA.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Panel on food safety. (1) There is a panel on food safety.
15 (2) The panel is allocated to the department of public health and human services for administrative
16 purposes only as prescribed in 2-15-121.
17 (3) The panel consists of six members.
18 (a) The governor shall appoint three members, who must have scientific expertise in:
19 (i) chemical risk assessment and safety assessment of food additives and flavoring substances;
20 (ii) toxicology;
21 (iii) toxicity testing;
22 (iv) toxicokinetics and toxicodynamics of substances;
23 (v) chemistry;
24 (vi) exposure assessment and consumption surveys; or
25 (vii) food technology.
26 (b) The speaker of the house shall appoint three members of the public to serve on the panel as
27 representatives of Montana society at large.
28 (c) A representative of the department of public health and human services may participate on the
