2 (4) Panel members shall serve staggered 4-year terms. A vacancy on the panel for an unexpired
3 term must be filled by appointment by the governor or the speaker of the house. A member who previously
4 served an abbreviated term may be reappointed for a full 4-year term.
5 (5) The panel shall meet quarterly.
6 (6) Panel members shall serve without compensation but may be reimbursed as provided in 2-18-
7 501 through 2-18-503.
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Panel on food safety -- purpose. The panel shall:
10 (1) consider and study the cumulative effect of food additives and color additives in the diet, as
11 well as any chemically or pharmacologically related substances in the diet;
12 (2) set the cumulative amounts that are safe based on the toxicity data the United States food and
13 drug administration has on food additives, consumption statistics, and cumulative effects; and
14 (3) advise and make recommendations to the department of public health and human services on
15 limiting the availability of food containing a food additive or a color additive determined to have a negative, toxic
16 effect.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Panel on food safety -- reporting. (1) (a) The panel shall compile and
19 submit reports to the department every 12 months.
20 (b) The department shall post a copy of the report on a state digital access system to ensure public
21 access to the report.
22 (2) The panel shall compile and submit a report to the environmental quality council biennially in
23 accordance with 5-11-210.
24 (3) (a) Within 2 years of [the effective date of this act], the panel shall issue a report providing a list
25 of additives for regulation that includes safe levels of additives based on the cumulative amount in the food
26 supply.
27 (b) The report must provide the rationale for the decision reached.
28 (c) The report issued by the panel must be supported by a majority of the panel members.
